Created: Nov. 15th, 2009

Music Videos that capture the artists at their bes

Tags:

 

  • U2 - Rattle and Hum

    The best concert DVD U2 has ever done. It covers their most creative period. One can feel the energy of the crowd in the songs that were recorded live. The best sound quality of any of their DVDs.

  • Tina Turner - One Last Time

    This concert DVD was shot in London England. At that time it was to be her last concert. The DVD leaves you in awe of the energy this woman puts into to her concerts and just how much she enjoys performing on stage.

  • Pink Floyd - In Concert

    This video leaves you marvelling at the great talent this band had. This DVD includes all of their greatest hits in a unbelievable concert. The sound quality is amazing.

  • Roy Orbison - Black & White Night

    Shot in black and white the year was 1988 at a small club. Some of his friends (Bruce Springsteen, Elvis Costello, James Brown, Bonnie Raitt and James Burton to name a few) backed up Roy on performing all of his great hits in this close intimate setting. You come away from the video realizing what a great talent Roy Orbison was and how much fun all of these super stars in their own right had this particular evening.

  • The Moody Blues - Live From Royal Albert Hall

    The Moody Blues were the first group to write full orchestral versions of their rock classics. The first being in 1967 with the classic album "In Days of Future Past". This DVD shows the fullness of their music.

  • Meat Loaf - 3 Bats Live

    This concert video is Meat Loaf at his showmanship best. His teaming with Jim Stienman brings a unique fullness to storytelling through music.

  • Paul McCartney - Back In The USA

    All of the great songs from his three collaborations: The Beatles, Wings and Paul McCartney Solo. A great concert to see.

  • Peter Gabriel - The Secret World Live

    Unique stage show from a very talented artist.

  • Fleetwood Mac - The Dance

    Their first appearance together in a number of years. Even after all of this time tehy still sound great.

  • The Eagles - Live From Melbourne

    Covers all of their great hits including those from the solo careers of Don Henley and Glenn Frey. Top quality sound
